### Tested versions

bisected to https://github.com/godotengine/godot/pull/105249

### System information

linux

### Issue description

spotlights with shadows enabled do not show up in voxelGI.

this was originally thought to be a problem with my PR and posted as a comment here https://github.com/godotengine/godot/pull/106673#issuecomment-2942714831, but it's not related to my PR.

I bisected the issue as a regression related to this PR https://github.com/godotengine/godot/pull/105249. the following patch which reverts the change for just `scene/3d/voxelizer.cpp` fixes it, but I'm not sure exactly why, so it might be worth looking at other instances of that PR that insert `Math::INF` because it could have caused other similar bugs.

```diff
diff --git a/scene/3d/voxelizer.cpp b/scene/3d/voxelizer.cpp
index 6dd0fda8cb..fbdc667a6e 100644
--- a/scene/3d/voxelizer.cpp
+++ b/scene/3d/voxelizer.cpp
@@ -816,6 +816,7 @@ Vector<int> Voxelizer::get_voxel_gi_level_cell_count() const {
 // https://prideout.net/blog/distance_fields/

 #define square(m_s) ((m_s) * (m_s))
+#define INF 1e20

 /* dt of 1d function using squared distance */
 static void edt(float *f, int stride, int n) {
@@ -825,8 +826,8 @@ static void edt(float *f, int stride, int n) {

 	int k = 0;
 	v[0] = 0;
-	z[0] = -Math::INF;
-	z[1] = +Math::INF;
+	z[0] = -INF;
+	z[1] = +INF;
 	for (int q = 1; q <= n - 1; q++) {
 		float s = ((f[q * stride] + square(q)) - (f[v[k] * stride] + square(v[k]))) / (2 * q - 2 * v[k]);
 		while (s <= z[k]) {
@@ -837,7 +838,7 @@ static void edt(float *f, int stride, int n) {
 		v[k] = q;

 		z[k] = s;
-		z[k + 1] = +Math::INF;
+		z[k + 1] = +INF;
 	}

 	k = 0;
@@ -861,7 +862,7 @@ Voxelizer::BakeResult Voxelizer::get_sdf_3d_image(Vector<uint8_t> &r_image, Bake
 	uint32_t float_count = octree_size.x * octree_size.y * octree_size.z;
 	float *work_memory = memnew_arr(float, float_count);
 	for (uint32_t i = 0; i < float_count; i++) {
-		work_memory[i] = Math::INF;
+		work_memory[i] = INF;
 	}

 	uint32_t y_mult = octree_size.x;
@@ -944,6 +945,8 @@ Voxelizer::BakeResult Voxelizer::get_sdf_3d_image(Vector<uint8_t> &r_image, Bake
 	return BAKE_RESULT_OK;
 }

+#undef INF
+
 void Voxelizer::_debug_mesh(int p_idx, int p_level, const AABB &p_aabb, Ref<MultiMesh> &p_multimesh, int &idx) {
 	if (p_level == cell_subdiv - 1) {
 		Vector3 center = p_aabb.get_center();
```

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/621e96df-cc50-477a-9f9e-52c2f7bfe311)
note that the harsh circle here is probably incorrect behavior which is fixed by my previously mentioned PR, but for the purposes of *this* issue, the problem is the complete lack of light on the right.

### Steps to reproduce

open the MRP, select the ShadowOn/VoxelGI node and click "Bake VoxelGI". note that since it's a problem with the voxelizer, not the renderer, it can appear wrong until you re-bake.

